biobridge stanford university browse available biology advisors w hat is biobridge it's an undergraduate peer advising group and informational resource for the department of biology biobridge advisors serve as a link to several aspects of the biology major via coordinating outreach programs for current and prospective biology majors being trained and knowledgeable about departmental requirements policies and procedures promoting interaction between the biology faculty and the undergraduate student population organizing informational programs and presentations specifically for biology majors on topics related to research grants employment and other post graduate opportunities upcoming event information session on hopkins marine station 7 00pm wed 26th october in old union rm 215 contact ian markham ipmarkham gmail com for more info questions email biobridge lists stanford edu or submit a question online
